Glossary
ChocAn member- Chocolate addicted person who is billed to access ChocAn services
Provider - A healthcare professional who has agreed to service ChocAn members
ID card- A plastic card given to ChocAn members encoded with their identifying information
ChocAn computer terminal- The machine that reads data from ID cards
ChocAn Data Center- Collects information from terminals and processes information requests
Provider Directory- Organized lists of all services and their providers currently available to ChocAn members
Weekly report- A financial/order history statement sent to all ChocAn members each week
EFT Data- Electronic funds transfer data which is used by the banking software to record and manage all funds transferred through ChocAn
Summary report- Weekly report sent to a ChocAn manager which lists all provider activities, including sessions and services, and the amount providers are owed



